Interface Clickable

All Known Implementing Classes:
CheckBox, Link, NullBrowserElement, RadioButton, TextArea, TextField, TinyMceEditor
public interface Clickable
extends BrowserElement

Interface that indicates that a browser element can be clicked. Unless absolutely needed do not make your page object implement this interface directly. Instead make them extend Link.

Method Detail

click_if_enabled

void click_if_enabled()
Click the element if it is enabled, i.e. isEnabled() returns true If the element is not displayed calling this method will throw AssertionError

click_if_exists_and_enabled

void click_if_exists_and_enabled()
Click the element if it is displayed and enabled, i.e. isDisplayed() returns true and isEnabled() returns true
